                            <comment id="14320384" author="hsaputra" created="Fri, 13 Feb 2015 16:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per discussion in dev list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about construct a Flink test directory under directory specified under &quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot; and change the permission to not allow create new directory.&lt;br/&gt;
Then the BlobUtilsTest.testExceptionOnCreateStorageDirectoryFailure test is set to try create &quot;cannot-create-this&quot; under this directory.&lt;br/&gt;
Something like:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Create /tmp/flink-blob-test-dir at @BeforeClass&lt;br/&gt;
2. Change permission to not able to write in here.&lt;br/&gt;
3. Try to create Blob store at  /tmp/flink-blob-test-dir/cannot-create-this&lt;br/&gt;
4. Throw exception&lt;br/&gt;
5. Clean up flink-blob-test-dir&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14320815" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 13 Feb 2015 21:47:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user hsaputra opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/396&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/396&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1542&quot; title=&quot;Test case at BlobUtilsTest should not assume user could not create new item in root directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-1542&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-1542&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Test case at BlobUtilsTest should not assume user could not create new item in root directory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Sometimes, user that run tests could have write access to root dir such as creating /cannot-create-this&lt;br/&gt;
    is possible, hence to exception thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Need to construct a Flink test directory under directory specified under &quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot; and change the permission to not allow create new&lt;br/&gt;
    directory.&lt;/p&gt;

